    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "html": "For each vowel sound in the left-hand column there are corresponding long and short vowels, and their forms may differ depending on whether they're in medial position (followed by a final consonant) or final position (where there's no final consonant). The vowels which are centred in the table only have one form and do not change."
